Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:35.922 --> 02:39.622
sync and corrections by bellows
www.addic7ed.com

03:15.285 --> 03:17.186
What the fuck
are you stopping for?

03:17.220 --> 03:18.921
- I'm hurting you.
- You're not hurting me.

03:18.955 --> 03:20.622
But you told me to hurt you.

03:20.657 --> 03:22.957
Then fucking hurt me!

03:39.508 --> 03:41.642
You okay?

03:43.645 --> 03:46.180
Mr. Rosetti?

03:46.215 --> 03:47.482
Gyp?

03:54.656 --> 03:57.091
Wet towel.

04:03.699 --> 04:05.901
I headed up there
as fast as I could.

04:05.935 --> 04:08.370
I tried to stop them,
they wouldn't listen.

04:08.404 --> 04:10.505
'Cause Mickey...

04:10.539 --> 04:13.809
'cause they were under
orders to get you

04:13.843 --> 04:15.643
<i>what you paid for.</i>

04:15.678 --> 04:18.579
- And yet you escaped.
- We lost 11 men.

04:18.613 --> 04:21.149
Was I supposed to get
myself killed, too?

04:25.421 --> 04:29.090
Rosetti controls the roads
in and out of Tabor Heights,

04:29.125 --> 04:31.326
taken up residence in the town,

04:31.361 --> 04:33.695
commandeered
the sheriff's department.

04:33.763 --> 04:36.264
He burned the sheriff.

04:36.299 --> 04:37.866
There are other routes.

04:37.900 --> 04:39.301
Don't you think
I've considered that?

04:39.335 --> 04:41.169
How about your million
dollar fucking highway?

04:41.204 --> 04:44.072
Must you swear
every time you speak?

04:44.106 --> 04:45.740
When did you become a Quaker?

04:45.775 --> 04:47.442
Firstly, it's no longer
my highway,

04:47.476 --> 04:50.178
and it costs considerably
more than a million dollars.

04:50.212 --> 04:52.780
Secondly, it's two years
away from being finished.

04:52.814 --> 04:55.850
Thirdly, the other routes
are not viable.

04:55.884 --> 04:57.020
What does that mean?

04:57.120 --> 04:58.720
To truck the quantities
you're talking about...

05:00.822 --> 05:02.956
Sorry, I interrupted.

05:03.891 --> 05:05.725
Go on.

05:06.760 --> 05:09.762
Well, between the mud
and the ice

05:09.796 --> 05:12.597
and the law, it's more
than we can manage.

05:12.632 --> 05:14.599
That's correct.

05:20.272 --> 05:22.340
Thanks for your input.

05:33.484 --> 05:36.286
Let's discuss our options.

05:38.022 --> 05:39.890
Our options?

05:39.924 --> 05:41.324
To solve this problem.

05:41.359 --> 05:43.827
How long have
you known Mr. Rosetti?

05:45.463 --> 05:47.598
A year or so. I don't know.
You were the one who introduced me.

05:47.632 --> 05:49.300
He kicks up to Joe Masseria.

05:51.369 --> 05:54.371
With whom I have
a very delicate truce.

05:54.406 --> 05:56.473
- Over what?
- <i>That's not your concern.</i>

05:56.507 --> 05:58.608
<i>But what might solve</i>
<i>a problem for you</i>

05:58.643 --> 06:00.777
creates a bigger one for me.

06:00.811 --> 06:02.645
And what would you do
about a mad dog?

06:02.680 --> 06:05.614
Before anything else, I'd
find out who its master was.

06:05.649 --> 06:08.151
Rosetti doesn't respect
any rules, Arnold.

06:08.185 --> 06:10.887
That makes him bad for
business, yours and mine.

06:10.921 --> 06:14.290
I'd like to talk to Mr.
Thompson in private, please.

06:23.568 --> 06:24.902
Bad for business?

06:24.936 --> 06:27.438
- Isn't it?
- What would you know about it?

06:27.472 --> 06:30.007
Conducting yours like
some drunken shopkeeper.

06:30.075 --> 06:32.677
All right, Arnold.
You're allowed to blow off steam.

06:32.711 --> 06:34.078
It's not all right.

06:34.112 --> 06:35.813
Do you think I entered
into this arrangement

06:35.847 --> 06:39.784
because I value
your companionship?

06:39.818 --> 06:42.319
You are a convenience

06:42.353 --> 06:44.755
of geography and supply.

06:44.790 --> 06:48.192
You promised a quantity
and a price.

06:48.227 --> 06:50.060
You have failed to deliver.

06:50.095 --> 06:53.597
And now, owing to your inability
to manage your own affairs

06:53.631 --> 06:55.165
in New Jersey,

06:55.199 --> 06:58.434
a state I have little interest
in or affection for,

06:58.469 --> 07:01.438
you expect me to start
a war in New York

07:01.472 --> 07:04.040
where things actually matter?

07:04.074 --> 07:07.643
I expect you to understand that Gyp
Rosetti is trouble for everyone.

07:07.677 --> 07:09.111
I lost an entire convoy.

07:09.146 --> 07:11.714
Because of your own
cavalierness.

07:11.748 --> 07:15.485
Because you run off to
Manhattan at a moment's notice

07:15.519 --> 07:17.688
to rut with some showgirl.

07:17.722 --> 07:20.557
- You'd be wise to leave Miss Kent
out of this. - Why? You can't.

07:20.591 --> 07:23.960
Do you even begin to understand
how weak that makes you look?

07:23.995 --> 07:26.496
That's a big noise from a man
who's dead below the waist.

07:26.531 --> 07:28.666
- I practice discretion.
- You practice bullshit.

07:28.700 --> 07:30.334
Who the fuck are you, Arnold?

07:30.368 --> 07:33.037
Aside from a little weasel
with a good poker face?

07:51.358 --> 07:53.192
- Charlie.
- A.R.

07:53.227 --> 07:54.961
Let's move on
to other business.

08:15.481 --> 08:17.482
Is there anything
I need to know?

08:17.516 --> 08:20.084
What time
is Billie's rehearsal?

08:20.119 --> 08:22.753
1:00.

08:24.256 --> 08:26.590
Take me to the house.

08:44.709 --> 08:46.877
Say, Georgie,
boss wants to see you.

08:46.912 --> 08:50.414
Did you perch a bucket of water
above his door jamb?

08:50.482 --> 08:53.484
Suspicious
son of a gun, ain't ya?

08:53.519 --> 08:56.921
What does he want
to see me about?

08:58.891 --> 09:01.760
Sounds like the feds
finally caught up with you.

09:17.945 --> 09:22.383
I got a call from the Bureau
of Internal Revenue.

09:25.987 --> 09:28.656
Where did you work before this?

09:32.294 --> 09:34.261
I thought I told you.

09:34.295 --> 09:37.664
I owned a wheat farm.

09:37.698 --> 09:41.134
And where was
this wheat farm exactly?

09:42.202 --> 09:45.938
Minnesota.
East of Ortonville.

09:47.774 --> 09:49.508
Now how hard was that?

09:49.542 --> 09:50.743
Sir?

09:50.777 --> 09:52.879
Your goshdang tax form,
it was incomplete.

09:55.582 --> 09:57.484
I don't have time for this
nonsense, George.

09:57.518 --> 09:59.553
<i>Your return is your own</i>
<i>responsibility.</i>

09:59.587 --> 10:02.957
Yes, sir. Yes, sir.
Of course it is.

10:02.991 --> 10:06.360
Oh, George.
A fellow left this for you.

10:06.394 --> 10:08.061
Says he met you in a speak.

10:10.265 --> 10:12.566
Not thinking of turning
us in, are you?

10:55.879 --> 10:57.980
Don't stand on
my account, Leander.

10:58.015 --> 10:59.715
It hurts too much to sit.

10:59.750 --> 11:01.484
What's wrong?

11:01.518 --> 11:03.285
Encroaching decrepitude.

11:03.320 --> 11:05.989
I thought you Yankees
were supposed to be stoic.

11:06.023 --> 11:07.690
Do you know what consoles me?

11:07.725 --> 11:09.859
I can't imagine.

11:09.894 --> 11:12.495
That this entire world will
be overrun by corruption,

11:12.529 --> 11:16.199
ignorance, and perfidy, but I
won't be forced to witness it.

11:16.233 --> 11:18.835
That does sound comforting.

11:18.870 --> 11:21.405
But perhaps we can
talk about me now.

11:21.440 --> 11:25.410
I've got some marvelous ideas for
the club that I'm eager to realize.

11:25.444 --> 11:27.512
The traditional
house of pleasure

11:27.546 --> 11:30.982
is hopelessly mired in
an outdated, button-tufted...

11:31.049 --> 11:33.784
2,100 a month in.

11:33.819 --> 11:36.054
2,700 a month out.

11:36.088 --> 11:37.755
I do wish you'd let me finish.

11:37.789 --> 11:39.156
This is what you
pay me to tell you.

11:39.191 --> 11:41.092
Your costs exceed your revenue.

11:41.159 --> 11:43.728
Every business takes time
to find its footing.

11:43.762 --> 11:45.329
And that cannot continue.

11:49.068 --> 11:52.970
The roof lets in buckets.
That's 800.

11:53.005 --> 11:56.207
There's a crack in the foundation.
That's 1,000.

11:56.275 --> 11:58.076
The sewer pipes collapsed.

11:58.111 --> 12:00.579
I haven't had the stomach
to get an estimate on that yet.

12:00.613 --> 12:03.448
I need your help
to arrange a loan

12:03.482 --> 12:05.316
to make it through to summer.

12:05.351 --> 12:08.019
- It always picks up then.
- Don't you have a partner?

12:08.054 --> 12:11.390
Mr. Luciano and I differ on
how the club should be run.

12:11.425 --> 12:12.992
Then you have to resolve that.

12:16.797 --> 12:18.765
This place, Leander...

12:20.834 --> 12:23.870
it's meant to be a dream.

12:25.140 --> 12:29.743
Every man who walks inside
is young and handsome.

12:29.811 --> 12:32.412
Every girl is innocent,

12:32.447 --> 12:34.815
trusting, and devoted.

12:34.849 --> 12:38.585
The light is flattering,
the air is perfumed,

12:38.619 --> 12:41.555
and nothing ever changes.

12:41.589 --> 12:44.925
Who doesn't need
to believe that?

12:44.959 --> 12:46.126
<i>Just for a little while?</i>

12:46.160 --> 12:47.995
We've been through
this, Gillian.

12:48.029 --> 12:51.064
- There's the house for collateral.
- <i>You don't own the house.</i>

12:51.099 --> 12:53.166
- My son does.
- Tommy is not your son.

12:53.201 --> 12:55.402
And in any case,
he doesn't own it either.

12:55.436 --> 12:57.804
- It's in James's name.
- That's who I'm talking about.

12:57.839 --> 12:59.907
Well, then,
before anything else,

12:59.942 --> 13:02.443
the process of having
him declared dead...

13:02.478 --> 13:05.180
- I really don't see the point.
- If you refuse to acknowledge...

13:05.214 --> 13:07.215
<i>He's prone to long</i>
<i>disappearances.</i>

13:07.249 --> 13:09.584
He's always been
an adventurous boy.

13:09.618 --> 13:11.552
Gillian!

13:11.586 --> 13:14.989
Until James is declared dead,
you have no ownership.

13:15.023 --> 13:18.091
You have no title.
You have no credit.

13:18.125 --> 13:21.394
And you're wasting
an old man's time.

13:43.120 --> 13:44.954
- What do you think?
- Better.

13:44.989 --> 13:48.591
But, "Do you wish
for greater knowledge?"

13:48.626 --> 13:50.259
Well, don't you?

13:50.294 --> 13:52.362
It sounds vaguely mystical.

13:52.396 --> 13:56.633
I can hardly write,
"Come discuss your vagina."

13:56.667 --> 13:59.235
Couldn't you put
a picture on it somewhere?

13:59.270 --> 14:01.004
Kittens, maybe.

14:02.573 --> 14:04.341
Hello again.

14:04.375 --> 14:05.909
Ladies.

14:05.943 --> 14:09.446
- Philip didn't let you in?
- Mr. Thompson used his key.

14:12.316 --> 14:14.684
Would you excuse me?

14:16.954 --> 14:20.590
Well, Mr. Sleater, do you
wish for greater knowledge?

14:20.625 --> 14:23.127
- You can take your hat off.
- I'm not staying.

14:23.162 --> 14:26.631
Actually, I have business
out of town for a few days.

14:26.665 --> 14:29.533
You needn't have come
to tell me that.

14:29.567 --> 14:31.803
Just wanted to make sure
everything's all right.

14:31.837 --> 14:33.937
- What's going on?
- Nothing.

14:34.005 --> 14:36.240
Then what is it
you're making sure about?

14:36.275 --> 14:38.476
That my family is safe.
Can't I do that?

14:38.510 --> 14:41.612
Are there to be
bodyguards again?

14:41.647 --> 14:44.148
Don't give me
that look, please.

14:44.183 --> 14:46.784
- What look? - The one that says
you know what I'm thinking.

14:46.819 --> 14:50.421
The state of my soul.
What I had for breakfast.

14:50.455 --> 14:52.990
I'm fairly certain
what you had for breakfast.

14:53.025 --> 14:55.226
The rest I wouldn't dare
speculate about.

14:55.260 --> 14:57.161
Will you answer my question?

14:57.195 --> 15:00.898
It's just a precaution.
There's no cause for concern.

15:00.933 --> 15:04.569
And it makes me feel better.
Where are the children?

15:04.604 --> 15:06.137
Out with Lillian.

15:06.172 --> 15:08.606
Is that dangerous?

15:08.641 --> 15:11.009
No. I just thought I'd...

15:11.043 --> 15:14.679
anyway, I bought them
each a copy

15:14.714 --> 15:16.982
so there's no fighting.

15:24.357 --> 15:25.990
What was that about?

15:27.259 --> 15:29.461
He worries sometimes.

15:33.132 --> 15:35.700
He couldn't figure
it out either.

15:35.735 --> 15:37.702
What?

15:39.071 --> 15:41.873
<i>The committee calls</i>
<i>Treasury Secretary</i>

15:41.908 --> 15:44.709
<i>Mr. Andrew W. Mellon.</i>

16:06.000 --> 16:07.500
I am ready.

16:07.534 --> 16:09.368
Thank you for taking the time

16:09.402 --> 16:11.404
to come here today,
Secretary Mellon.

16:13.273 --> 16:15.842
I assume there is something
you wanted to ask me.

16:15.876 --> 16:17.210
<i>Indeed there is.</i>

16:17.244 --> 16:19.212
Could you speak
to the committee

16:19.246 --> 16:23.416
concerning your views on the state
of Prohibition at this time?

16:23.450 --> 16:26.786
My views on that subject
are well known.

16:26.821 --> 16:30.423
Nonetheless, could you
summarize, Mr. Secretary?

16:32.093 --> 16:34.694
Setting aside
my own personal view

16:34.729 --> 16:36.563
as to the questionable wisdom

16:36.597 --> 16:39.933
of pandering to the demands
of a minority,

16:39.968 --> 16:43.203
I believe I have been
quite clear that the cost

16:43.237 --> 16:46.573
of effectively policing this act
would be somewhere in the amount

16:46.608 --> 16:49.676
of 28 millions
of dollars per annum...

16:51.246 --> 16:53.947
approximately five times

16:53.981 --> 16:57.217
what Congress has seen fit
to authorize.

16:57.251 --> 17:00.287
Would you not consider that, sir,
throwing good money after bad?

17:00.321 --> 17:03.323
That is a question that would
have been better asked

17:03.357 --> 17:06.159
before the amendment
was voted on in 1919.

17:06.194 --> 17:08.595
May I remind my fellow senators

17:08.628 --> 17:11.765
that the focus of these
hearings is not enforcement,

17:11.799 --> 17:13.767
but prosecution?

17:13.800 --> 17:15.836
In that case,

17:15.869 --> 17:18.238
you are speaking
to the wrong man.

17:18.306 --> 17:20.874
Oh, we fully intend to call
Attorney General Daugherty

17:20.907 --> 17:22.342
before this committee.

17:22.377 --> 17:25.979
But what we're seeking today
is a sense of to what degree

17:26.012 --> 17:29.349
the efforts by your bureau
may or may not

17:29.383 --> 17:32.185
be undermined
by the Department of Justice.

17:32.219 --> 17:35.488
You have been presented
with tables

17:35.522 --> 17:38.091
laying out the number
of arrests

17:38.125 --> 17:39.726
versus the number
of convictions?

17:39.793 --> 17:42.362
I, um...

17:51.205 --> 17:52.672
Yes, we have it right here.

17:52.706 --> 17:55.875
Then you are free to draw
your own conclusions.

17:55.909 --> 17:57.710
I don't see what all
this pussyfooting is for.

17:57.745 --> 18:00.780
Mr. Mellon, are we talking
about gross incompetence

18:00.815 --> 18:04.617
inside the Justice Department
or widespread corruption?

18:04.652 --> 18:07.687
It is my experience

18:07.721 --> 18:11.157
that human nature leaves
ample room for both.

18:23.001 --> 18:24.902
Excuse me.

18:24.936 --> 18:28.839
I believe your left shoelace
is in a state of dishabille.

18:34.412 --> 18:36.346
Now Mellon is in
there talking to them.

18:36.414 --> 18:38.181
I ascertained that
already, Harvey.

18:38.215 --> 18:40.416
But what is he talking about?

18:40.451 --> 18:43.486
Your boss's dirty hands.

